The paper analyzes user complaints about mobile in-app ads, which involves aspects of human-computer interaction (HCI) and information retrieval (IR) as users interact with and search for apps with desirable ad features. Additionally, the paper may involve multimedia (MM) aspects as ads may include images or videos. The analysis of user reviews also involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques, which falls under the sub-category of computational linguistics (CL). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.HC and cs.IR, followed by cs.MM, cs.SI, and cs.CL.
